narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Take it if you want to write two fairly intense papers and have s good weekly discussion. Don't take it if you're not down for some theoretical discussion.
The class is super interesting and fun. It presented a new way to think about form and the syllabus is very unique. If you like the look of the syllabus, I say go for it!

I would recommend this course to self-directed students who want the time to develop their own thinking about a text or movie, or to ambitious students who have less experience with literary analysis but would like to begin thinking more seriously about it.
I would highly recommend this course if you are interested in digging deeply into the form and substance of a text. The reading/viewing list is engaging and the discussion is generally high level.
